# Integration Guidelines

## Module Integration

### Frontend → Backend
- React components → REST API calls → Flask endpoints
- TypeScript API client handles authentication and requests
- JWT tokens stored in localStorage

### Backend → Database
- Flask-SQLAlchemy ORM for database operations
- PostgreSQL for persistent storage
- User authentication and document history

### Backend → AI Service
- Flask services → Google Gemini API
- Prompt engine constructs structured prompts
- Error handling for API failures

## External Dependencies

### Frontend
- React with TypeScript
- API client libraries (fetch/axios)

### Backend
- Flask: Web framework
- Flask-SQLAlchemy: ORM
- Flask-JWT-Extended: JWT authentication
- google-generativeai: Google Gemini API client
- PostgreSQL: Database

## Data Flow

1. User submits email/report generation request (Frontend)
2. Request authenticated via JWT (Backend)
3. Prompt constructed from user input (Prompt Engine)
4. Content generated via Google Gemini API (AI Service)
5. Generated content stored in database (PostgreSQL)
6. Response returned to frontend (Backend → Frontend)
7. User views generated content (Frontend)

## API Integration Points

- `/api/auth/login`: User authentication
- `/api/auth/register`: User registration
- `/api/documents/email:generate`: Email generation
- `/api/documents/report:generate`: Report generation
- `/api/history`: Document history retrieval
- `/api/admin/*`: Admin operations
